      <p>INFJs are most fulfilled in careers that align with their values, leverage their empathy and insight, and allow them to make a meaningful impact on others' lives. They wilt in purely transactional, high-pressure sales, or highly bureaucratic environments that lack purpose. The following table highlights career paths that tend to suit the INFJ's strengths and motivations.</p>

